From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: GitHub Copilot <noreply@github.com>
Date: Sun, 1 Jun 2026 13:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] ANDROID: GKI: always include devices cgroup subsystem for ABI stability

When CONFIG_CGROUP_DEVICE is enabled, SUBSYS(devices) inserts the
devices subsystem into the cgroup_subsys_id enum between memory and
freezer, shifting freezer_cgrp_id and net_prio_cgrp_id and breaking
vendor modules compiled against the original IDs.

Fix by making SUBSYS(devices) unconditional to keep CGROUP_SUBSYS_COUNT
and all subsequent subsystem IDs stable. A no-op stub devices_cgrp_subsys
is provided in security/device_cgroup.c when CONFIG_CGROUP_DEVICE is
disabled.

Change-Id: I0000000000000000000000000000000000000001
Signed-off-by: GitHub Copilot <noreply@github.com>
---
 include/linux/cgroup_subsys.h | 5 ++---
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/include/linux/cgroup_subsys.h b/include/linux/cgroup_subsys.h
--- a/include/linux/cgroup_subsys.h
+++ b/include/linux/cgroup_subsys.h
@@ -29,9 +29,12 @@ SUBSYS(io)
 SUBSYS(memory)
 #endif
 
-#if IS_ENABLED(CONFIG_CGROUP_DEVICE)
+/*
+ * Always include devices cgroup subsystem to keep CGROUP_SUBSYS_COUNT
+ * stable for GKI ABI compatibility. A no-op stub is provided in
+ * security/device_cgroup.c when CONFIG_CGROUP_DEVICE is disabled.
+ */
 SUBSYS(devices)
-#endif
 
 #if IS_ENABLED(CONFIG_CGROUP_FREEZER)
 SUBSYS(freezer)
-- 
